\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The school day had ended, and the hallways buzzed with the chatter of students heading to clubs, cram school, or home. Haruhi walked briskly toward the Art Club room, her bag slung over one shoulder and her sketchbook tucked under her arm. Aiko trailed behind her, trying to keep up while simultaneously prying more information out of her friend.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You know,\u8221\'94 Aiko said, her tone a mix of exasperation and admiration, \u8220\'93I thought you\u8217\'92d at least talk with your parents and try to convince them, Haruhi. You know, like, make a PowerPoint presentation or something. \u8216\'91Top Ten Reasons Why I Should Go to Art School.\u8217\'92\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruhi smirked but didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t slow her pace. \u8220\'93I talked with my mom,\u8221\'94 she said simply.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Aiko raised an eyebrow. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And your dad?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He wasn\u8217\'92t around,\u8221\'94 Haruhi replied, her voice casual. \u8220\'93But I don\u8217\'92t think he\u8217\'92d care.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Aiko stopped in her tracks, her mouth dropping open. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 crazy}{\f0\fs24\b0 ,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 she said, her voice rising. \u8220\'93Do you even hear yourself? Your dad\u8217\'92s, like, the CEO of a major company. Of course he\u8217\'92d care!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruhi paused and turned to face Aiko, her expression calm but firm. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, he\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 wasn\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92t around}{\f0\fs24\b0 ,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 she repeated, emphasizing each word. \u8220\'93He\u8217\'92s never around. He\u8217\'92s too busy with work to care about what I do.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Aiko stared at her, her usual playful demeanor replaced by genuine concern. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Haruhi\u8230\'85\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruhi sighed and looked away, her grip tightening on her sketchbook. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Look, I know it sounds reckless, but I can\u8217\'92t keep waiting for their approval. If I do, I\u8217\'92ll never get to live my life. I have to take this step, even if it\u8217\'92s scary.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Aiko was silent for a moment, then she stepped forward and placed a hand on Haruhi\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s shoulder. \u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re braver than I\u8217\'92ll ever be,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice soft. \u8220\'93But just\u8230\'85 be careful, okay? Your parents aren\u8217\'92t exactly the forgiving type.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruhi nodded, a small smile tugging at her lips. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know. But I\u8217\'92ll figure it out. I always do.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Aiko grinned and punched her lightly on the arm. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s the spirit! Now, let\u8217\'92s get to the Art Club before someone steals all the good paintbrushes.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruhi laughed, the tension in her chest easing slightly. As they continued down the hallway, she couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help but feel a sense of relief. For the first time in a long time, she felt like she was moving forward, even if the path ahead was uncertain.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But as they turned the corner toward the Art Club room, Haruhi\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s smile faded slightly. She knew the real challenges were still to come. Her parents would find out about her decision eventually, and when they did, there would be no turning back.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Still, she couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help but feel a flicker of hope. She had taken the first step, and that was something no one could take away from her.}
